    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Timeframe</th>
          <th>Accuracy</th>
          <th>Reliability</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>0-3 hours (nowcast)</td>
          <td>85-90%</td>
          <td>‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê Excellent</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>3-24 hours</td>
          <td>70-80%</td>
          <td>‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê Good</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>1-3 days</td>
          <td>50-70%</td>
          <td>‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê Moderate</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>3-7 days</td>
          <td>30-50%</td>
          <td>‚≠ê‚≠ê Low (unreliable)</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>
      <strong>Why accuracy drops:</strong> Solar wind can change speed/direction unexpectedly. Coronal mass ejections (CMEs) may arrive earlier/later than predicted.
    </p>

    <div style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <KpIndexScale currentKp={5} requiredKp={3} showLabels={true} />
      <p style="text-align: center; color: #8A8A8A; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 0.5rem;">
        Example: Current Kp 5 exceeds required Kp 3 = aurora visible (green zone)
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

