    <p>
      High Kp means nothing if clouds are overhead. Always check:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Cloud coverage:</strong> <a href="https://www.windy.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Windy.com</a> or local weather</li>
      <li><strong>Target:</strong> Less than 30% clouds for good visibility</li>
      <li><strong>Timing:</strong> Check hourly forecast (clouds can clear suddenly)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Step 4: Calculate Darkness Window</h3>
    <p>
      Aurora is only visible in complete darkness (after nautical twilight ends). Check sunset/twilight times at <a href="https://www.timeanddate.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TimeAndDate.com</a>.
    </p>

    <div class="guide__info-box guide__info-box--warning">
